20:17.718 --> 20:19.485
And get this,

20:19.520 --> 20:20.253
one of my close friends

20:20.286 --> 20:23.223
is a headhunter.

20:23.256 --> 20:25.358
Eugene's put his name
out there.

20:26.192 --> 20:27.493
What?

20:27.528 --> 20:28.729
Eugene?

20:28.762 --> 20:29.763
STRINGER: Three weeks ago,
he interviewed

20:29.796 --> 20:31.264
at Hollings and Gray.

20:31.732 --> 20:34.601
That's not even the point.

20:34.635 --> 20:37.070
You have to go do this

20:37.103 --> 20:39.172
because it's what
you want to do.

20:42.275 --> 20:43.877
You have to do it.

20:55.989 --> 20:57.457
ROSE: It's not just
going away, Matthew,

20:57.490 --> 20:58.859
especially not quickly.

20:58.892 --> 20:59.660
He raped her.

20:59.693 --> 21:01.067
Not what I want to hear.

21:01.101 --> 21:03.436
Look, get the new guy
to do this.

21:03.469 --> 21:04.705
He's done criminal cases.
The new guy...

21:04.738 --> 21:07.373
is in court
on Denny Crane control.

21:07.407 --> 21:08.875
I told you when I came here

21:08.909 --> 21:12.145
it was to get away
from criminal law.

21:12.178 --> 21:13.980
I have an official
complaint to lodge,

21:14.014 --> 21:15.215
and since it's about her,

21:15.248 --> 21:16.983
she might as well
be present for it.

21:17.017 --> 21:18.585
I fight my battles open.

21:18.619 --> 21:20.821
You might want to opt
for an adverb there, Sal,

21:20.854 --> 21:22.789
"Openly" would support
your predicate.

21:22.823 --> 21:26.126
"Open" would describe
your leg position at the bar.

21:26.159 --> 21:27.160
HEEP: I want that
on the record.

21:27.193 --> 21:29.563
HALL: Ooh, the girls
are fighting.

21:29.596 --> 21:30.496
I've got a big one, Glenn.

21:30.531 --> 21:31.798
Yeah, tell me something
I don't know.

21:31.832 --> 21:33.266
Oh, please.

21:33.299 --> 21:34.601
Hannah.

21:34.635 --> 21:35.569
Glenn.

21:35.602 --> 21:37.070
Date rape, we need to find

21:37.103 --> 21:38.739
some credibility issues quickly.

21:38.772 --> 21:41.041
The victim's name
is Candace Watson.

21:41.074 --> 21:42.709
Suspect's father
is a blue chip.

21:42.743 --> 21:43.844
We'll get you employee records,

21:43.877 --> 21:45.846
school transcripts,
credit report.

21:45.879 --> 21:47.881
Your hair,

21:47.914 --> 21:49.115
it's so you.

21:49.149 --> 21:50.316
Mmm.

21:52.085 --> 21:52.786
Hi.

21:52.819 --> 21:53.954
Hi.

21:54.354 --> 21:56.289
We're not simply looking
to prevail at trial.

21:56.322 --> 21:58.324
The goal would be
to squash this now.

22:00.767 --> 22:01.835
I need this.

22:08.909 --> 22:09.576
(scoffs)

22:12.178 --> 22:13.880
Denny, I am begging you,

22:13.914 --> 22:15.982
I've prepared this opening
for three weeks.

22:16.016 --> 22:17.183
Overkill.

22:18.251 --> 22:19.920
(sighs) Alan...

22:21.855 --> 22:22.889
We don't want to steal
the thunder

22:22.923 --> 22:24.190
from your closing, Denny.

22:24.224 --> 22:26.660
Not gonna get
to a closing, no, sir.

22:27.093 --> 22:28.261
WHITE: Mr. Crane,

22:31.197 --> 22:32.465
we'll hear from you.

22:37.470 --> 22:38.505
CRANE: Denny Crane,

22:38.539 --> 22:40.140
I represent the plaintiff.

22:40.173 --> 22:41.675
And here's what's gonna happen.

22:41.708 --> 22:44.110
A whole lot of witnesses
