22:44.144 --> 22:45.946
tell you how and why...

22:45.979 --> 22:47.848
All Shop's lighting fixture

22:47.881 --> 22:49.983
fell on Mary Finnerty's head,

22:50.016 --> 22:52.586
killing her.

22:52.619 --> 22:54.655
The defense is gonna get up,
have their say,

22:54.688 --> 22:56.690
then I'll get up again

22:56.723 --> 22:58.525
and ask you to give...

22:58.559 --> 23:00.366
Sarah and Bill Finnerty

23:00.400 --> 23:01.835
a whole lot of money.

23:01.868 --> 23:04.237
Now, it's difficult to put a...

23:04.270 --> 23:07.107
price on a human life,
I grant you,

23:07.140 --> 23:09.743
but this is All Shop.

23:09.776 --> 23:11.077
And as the defense counsel

23:11.111 --> 23:13.313
was so quick
to point out to me,

23:13.346 --> 23:15.882
they have over 3,000 stores
in this country,

23:15.916 --> 23:17.651
10,000 internationally.

23:17.684 --> 23:20.587
We're not talking about
one lighting fixture.

23:20.621 --> 23:22.889
We're talking about a lot
of lives at stake here.

23:22.923 --> 23:24.257
Objection.

23:24.290 --> 23:25.458
Sustained.

23:25.491 --> 23:27.628
Mr. Crane, can we talk
about this case only?

23:27.661 --> 23:28.695
Can we do that?

23:28.729 --> 23:29.796
Oh, of course.

23:29.830 --> 23:31.497
I'm sorry, Your Honor.

23:42.876 --> 23:44.210
Um...

23:55.221 --> 23:57.758
value of human life,

23:59.125 --> 24:00.433
it's a bugger.

24:01.467 --> 24:03.036
My friend Jerry Spence
tells the story

24:03.069 --> 24:05.338
of this paper boy
delivering his papers

24:05.371 --> 24:06.673
on his morning route one day.

24:06.707 --> 24:08.441
He throws the paper
through the window,

24:08.474 --> 24:11.011
shatters the glass,

24:11.044 --> 24:12.813
blinds a woman.

24:15.348 --> 24:17.017
What's the value of that?

24:19.586 --> 24:22.556
The paper boy decides
to give the woman

24:24.024 --> 24:25.959
his profits for the week,
not very much,

24:25.992 --> 24:28.094
considering she was blinded.

24:28.128 --> 24:31.264
Now, here
we have a loss of life,

24:31.297 --> 24:32.933
an avoidable loss,

24:32.966 --> 24:35.135
not merely an accident,

24:35.168 --> 24:38.138
one they could have prevented.

24:38.171 --> 24:40.807
So, I think the paper boy
had the right idea.

24:40.841 --> 24:42.809
At the end of this trial,
I'm gonna get up,

24:42.843 --> 24:44.477
I'm gonna ask the defendant

24:44.511 --> 24:46.913
to pay my client
one week's profit.

24:48.114 --> 24:50.951
No, let's make that
a day's profit.

24:50.984 --> 24:53.119
Let's not get greedy here.

24:53.153 --> 24:54.320
We may not be able
to put a price

24:54.354 --> 24:55.922
on Mary Finnerty's life,

24:55.956 --> 24:59.325
but we can at least
pay her family

24:59.359 --> 25:02.035
the profits for the day
they killed her.

25:03.670 --> 25:05.772
What could be more
fair than that?

25:07.340 --> 25:08.074
Hmm?

25:10.744 --> 25:12.913
My client's profits
are not relevant.

25:13.514 --> 25:16.316
The number of stores
they have is not relevant.

25:16.349 --> 25:18.118
How dare you go into that?

25:18.685 --> 25:20.153
And how dare you
not shut him down?

25:20.654 --> 25:22.889
CRANE: May I go off
the record briefly?

25:22.923 --> 25:24.090
Go right ahead.

25:24.124 --> 25:25.125
Thank you.

25:25.158 --> 25:27.928
This is not for your ears,
by the way.

25:28.695 --> 25:30.463
You stupid bastard.

25:30.496 --> 25:32.533
Cases rarely turn on
what's legally relevant.

25:32.566 --> 25:34.868
What you have
to be concerned with here

25:34.901 --> 25:37.671
is that All Shop makes
$160 million

25:37.704 --> 25:39.573
of pure profit a day, a day,

25:39.606 --> 25:41.542
in gross revenues,
$800 million.

25:41.575 --> 25:42.876
In the 20 minutes
it took the ambulance

25:42.909 --> 25:45.579
to reach Mary Finnerty's
crushed head,

25:45.612 --> 25:47.748
your client took in $10 million.

25:48.481 --> 25:49.716
That might slip out in court,

25:49.750 --> 25:51.251
and even if it doesn't,

25:51.284 --> 25:52.352
look at this face.

25:52.385 --> 25:54.354
It comes with its own publicist.

25:54.387 --> 25:56.557
The jury will get wind
of those numbers.

25:56.590 --> 25:58.258
In which case, we'll appeal.

25:58.291 --> 25:59.392
CRANE: Great.
And do you think

25:59.425 --> 26:01.101
you'll be the lawyers
to handle that appeal

26:01.134 --> 26:02.168
when your client gets whacked

26:02.202 --> 26:04.505
with a $50-million judgment?

26:04.538 --> 26:06.072
You're an ass.

26:06.106 --> 26:07.207
You're an ass.

26:07.240 --> 26:09.275
You're an ass.

26:09.309 --> 26:11.545
How about we settle this case

26:11.578 --> 26:13.814
like your careers
depended on it?

26:15.582 --> 26:17.417
Dumb bastards.

26:17.450 --> 26:19.219
I'm sorry.
Where were we?

26:23.189 --> 26:24.758
Leaving?

26:24.791 --> 26:25.992
BERLUTI: I've been thinking
about this

26:26.026 --> 26:28.394
for a long time,
and now--

26:28.428 --> 26:29.763
Because you couldn't
take that case?

26:29.796 --> 26:31.898
In part, yes.

26:31.932 --> 26:34.000
The truth is,
I've always wanted

26:34.034 --> 26:35.335
to hang my own shingle.

26:35.368 --> 26:36.670
I'm 43 years old.

26:36.703 --> 26:38.972
If I don't do it now,
when, then?

26:39.005 --> 26:40.974
Considering what we're
going through now,

26:41.007 --> 26:42.408
how can you even think
of leaving?

26:42.776 --> 26:43.644
You are.

26:44.978 --> 26:47.447
You interviewed with Hollings
and Gray last month.

26:48.615 --> 26:49.950
FRUTT: Is that true, Eugene?

26:49.983 --> 26:51.084
They called
for an interview.

26:51.117 --> 26:51.918
I declined.

26:51.952 --> 26:53.019
No, you didn't.

26:53.053 --> 26:54.087
I declined the job.

26:54.120 --> 26:55.922
But not the interview.

26:55.956 --> 26:58.158
You considered leaving, Eugene.

26:58.191 --> 26:59.325
That's what I've been doing.

26:59.359 --> 27:01.467
We just came
to different conclusions.

27:01.501 --> 27:03.604
Do you have any idea
how difficult

27:03.637 --> 27:05.271
it would be
to launch a practice?

27:05.305 --> 27:06.840
Probably not,

27:06.873 --> 27:09.743
but I'm not coming
totally from logic here.

27:09.776 --> 27:11.411
This is emotional.

27:11.444 --> 27:13.013
FRUTT: Given that,

27:13.046 --> 27:15.115
why don't you at least wait

27:15.148 --> 27:17.618
to see if this impulse passes?

27:18.251 --> 27:19.620
The truth is, Ellenor,

27:19.653 --> 27:22.055
I've been wanting to leave
for a hundred years.

27:23.089 --> 27:25.058
I love this and all of you,

27:25.091 --> 27:27.661
don't get me wrong,

27:27.694 --> 27:29.462
but what I really want to do,

27:29.495 --> 27:32.132
deep down,

27:32.165 --> 27:33.166
this isn't it.

27:35.969 --> 27:38.605
I'll pitch in, handle cases,

27:38.639 --> 27:41.875
whatever you need.
I won't abandon you.

27:41.908 --> 27:43.777
But I got to do this.

27:45.746 --> 27:47.848
(sighs)

27:47.881 --> 27:49.616
And when would you do this?

27:51.251 --> 27:52.653
Today.

27:52.686 --> 27:54.420
It needs to be now.

28:00.133 --> 28:02.235
HEEP: I'm sick of her
not respecting me.

28:02.268 --> 28:03.737
I made law review
at Holy Cross,

28:03.770 --> 28:05.506
top 10% of my class,

28:05.539 --> 28:06.840
and people totally dismiss me

28:06.873 --> 28:08.341
because of the way I dress.

28:11.144 --> 28:13.313
Well, then,
let's talk about your dress.

28:13.346 --> 28:16.016
HEEP: I get clients because
of the way I look, Matthew.

28:16.049 --> 28:17.383
People approach me--

28:17.417 --> 28:18.852
Men approach you.

28:18.885 --> 28:20.887
Yes, many of whom
go on to hire me.

28:20.921 --> 28:24.324
And is that how you plan
to carve out your career?

28:28.261 --> 28:29.663
You know, you're right.

28:31.097 --> 28:34.434
Law review,
top 10% of your class,

28:34.467 --> 28:37.103
firms all over town should have
been extending offers.

28:38.705 --> 28:40.140
How many did?

28:44.077 --> 28:46.112
Sally, you're an attorney.

28:48.949 --> 28:52.085
I'm also 25, and I'm not
gonna dress like I'm 40.

28:53.253 --> 28:55.255
My legal skills
are excellent.

28:55.288 --> 28:57.057
I shouldn't get punished

28:57.090 --> 28:58.291
because my skirts are short.

28:58.324 --> 29:01.001
And you can tell Hannah
I'm gonna hit her.

29:01.034 --> 29:02.603
I don't care
if she's a partner.

29:02.636 --> 29:03.737
If she keeps treating me
like this,

29:03.770 --> 29:05.138
I'm gonna hit her.

29:09.209 --> 29:12.145
(crying)

29:13.847 --> 29:14.815
I'm sorry.

29:16.883 --> 29:17.818
According to the seminars,

29:17.851 --> 29:19.920
I'm not supposed to hug you,

29:22.288 --> 29:24.157
but I'm gonna risk it.

29:26.092 --> 29:28.662
Hey, hey, hey. Shh.

29:28.695 --> 29:30.430
(crying)

29:30.463 --> 29:32.733
Shh. Oh, hey. It's okay.

29:33.900 --> 29:35.235
It's okay.

29:37.671 --> 29:38.839
HALL: Munchausen's,

29:38.872 --> 29:41.274
basically, it's a disorder
that causes people

29:41.307 --> 29:43.109
to make up or fake diseases.

29:43.143 --> 29:43.844
ROSE: I know what it is.

29:43.877 --> 29:45.378
Where did you get this?

29:45.411 --> 29:47.013
I should say,
how did you get this?

29:47.047 --> 29:49.215
I don't think you mean
to ask me that.

29:49.249 --> 29:52.485
Was she ever actually
diagnosed with Munchausen's?

29:52.519 --> 29:54.320
She doesn't have it.

29:55.522 --> 29:57.257
Then why is she
on a hospital list?

29:57.290 --> 29:59.125
HALL: It's computer generated.

29:59.159 --> 30:01.668
If a person is admitted
for treatment over and over,

30:01.702 --> 30:03.704
the name eventually might end up

30:03.737 --> 30:05.939
on a possible
Munchausen list.

30:07.240 --> 30:09.475
Even if the injuries are legit?

30:09.510 --> 30:10.877
Shouldn't happen,

30:10.911 --> 30:12.913
but one doctor along the way
had to wonder

30:12.946 --> 30:15.882
whether she was really
abused by her father.

30:15.916 --> 30:17.417
That's enough.

30:28.161 --> 30:29.162
Do you have a second?

30:31.231 --> 30:32.398
Sure.

30:37.704 --> 30:38.939
I'm gonna ask you this

30:38.972 --> 30:41.074
in a quiet,
refrained tone,

30:41.107 --> 30:43.043
so as not to seem like
I'm attacking you.

30:44.545 --> 30:45.679
How is it you could interview

30:45.712 --> 30:47.213
with another law firm at--

30:47.247 --> 30:48.682
YOUNG: Ellenor,

30:48.715 --> 30:50.116
they wanted to meet.

30:50.150 --> 30:51.552
I told them I was not
interested.

30:51.585 --> 30:53.820
They were persistent
about at least talking.

30:53.854 --> 30:55.956
I only agreed to hear them out.

30:55.989 --> 30:57.023
I did.

30:57.057 --> 30:58.258
I restated my position,

30:58.291 --> 31:00.500
that I had no interest
in leaving here,

31:00.534 --> 31:01.902
and that was the end of it.

31:01.935 --> 31:04.838
Was that before
or after you fired Alan?

31:05.539 --> 31:09.209
It was after the firm voted
to discharge Alan Shore.

31:10.243 --> 31:12.913
Eugene, I don't think
I need to lecture you

31:12.946 --> 31:15.248
on the importance
of perception.

31:15.281 --> 31:19.119
But for us, during an incredibly
vulnerable period,

31:19.152 --> 31:22.756
for our senior partner
to be seen interviewing--

31:22.789 --> 31:23.857
Nobody saw.

31:24.390 --> 31:25.491
The word was out.

31:25.526 --> 31:26.492
Jamie heard it.

31:26.527 --> 31:27.561
She told Jimmy.

31:27.594 --> 31:29.195
The word got out.

31:30.797 --> 31:33.199
Forget that I'm your partner.

31:34.868 --> 31:36.803
As your friend,

31:36.837 --> 31:38.104
if you're planning to bail--

31:38.739 --> 31:40.273
I'm not bailing.

31:42.108 --> 31:43.443
(sighs)

31:45.912 --> 31:47.614
Are we gonna survive, Eugene?

31:50.083 --> 31:52.519
We'll survive.

31:52.553 --> 31:54.955
I'm not bailing,

31:54.988 --> 31:56.723
and we'll survive.

32:02.703 --> 32:03.537
(sighs)

32:07.574 --> 32:09.109
What can I tell his father?

32:09.142 --> 32:11.311
That I'm meeting
with the D. A. This morning.

32:11.344 --> 32:12.278
Other than that,

32:13.614 --> 32:14.314
Tara...

32:14.347 --> 32:15.849
Copies of cases,

32:15.882 --> 32:17.050
first circuit's on top,

32:17.083 --> 32:18.819
Massachusetts
is the second tab,

32:18.852 --> 32:21.722
dictum and legislative
intent after that.

32:21.755 --> 32:22.556
Would you like me
to come with you?

32:22.589 --> 32:24.224
I would, actually,

32:24.257 --> 32:26.292
but I'm too afraid you'll talk.

32:32.666 --> 32:34.234
Would it kill you
to be kind?

32:34.768 --> 32:36.837
Actually, I was once,
and it almost did.

32:36.870 --> 32:39.973
Ah, so I get the blame
for how you treat people.

32:40.006 --> 32:42.509
Just the opposite,
I give you total credit.

32:44.545 --> 32:46.947
Hannah, I would hate
to be the only one

32:46.980 --> 32:48.615
to experience the tender you.

32:50.884 --> 32:52.085
It's late.

32:52.118 --> 32:53.854
I've got to go do good deeds.

32:59.626 --> 33:02.168
Sheldon, I heard you settled.

33:02.202 --> 33:03.236
Yeah.

33:03.269 --> 33:04.705
$6.5 million.

33:04.738 --> 33:06.507
Good result,
the client's pleased.

33:06.540 --> 33:08.008
$6.5 million...

33:08.041 --> 33:10.511
you were stuck between
$1.2 million and $2.3 million.

33:10.544 --> 33:11.612
How did you get $6.5 million?

33:12.879 --> 33:15.215
Denny did good work.

33:15.248 --> 33:16.917
So I don't need
to intervene today?

33:23.957 --> 33:25.626
Don't you love it here?

33:29.429 --> 33:33.199
These convictions
are extremely difficult to get,

33:33.233 --> 33:35.602
especially when the suspect
and victim

33:35.636 --> 33:38.038
once had
a consensual relationship.

33:38.071 --> 33:39.673
Well, their relationship--

33:39.706 --> 33:41.908
I'm not saying I won't get it.

33:41.942 --> 33:44.911
I'm just trying
to prepare you, Mr. Watson.

33:46.379 --> 33:47.480
(knocks on door)

33:48.114 --> 33:50.183
Kenny, I, uh...

33:50.216 --> 33:51.084
oh, I'm sorry.

33:51.117 --> 33:52.418
I didn't know you were busy.

33:54.054 --> 33:55.722
Actually, I did.

33:57.290 --> 33:59.593
(sighs) You're
Candace Watson's father?

33:59.626 --> 34:00.567
I am.

34:01.167 --> 34:02.402
Hannah Rose,

34:02.435 --> 34:03.704
I have the unfortunate task

34:03.737 --> 34:04.605
of defending the man

34:04.638 --> 34:05.438
who raped your daughter,

34:05.471 --> 34:07.007
who, between the three of us,

34:07.040 --> 34:08.775
I'm convinced is guilty.

34:09.676 --> 34:10.811
What do you want, Hannah?

34:10.844 --> 34:13.547
In the interest
of no surprises,

34:13.580 --> 34:14.414
medical report,

34:15.415 --> 34:18.150
a claim you once
abused your daughter.

34:19.284 --> 34:20.954
I'm sure you didn't.

34:20.987 --> 34:22.455
A hospital turned up her name

34:22.487 --> 34:23.956
as a possible Munchausen's.

34:23.989 --> 34:24.925
What is going on?
WALSH: Hannah, if you

34:24.958 --> 34:25.891
could excuse us, please?

34:25.926 --> 34:27.460
If she makes things up--

34:27.493 --> 34:28.293
WALSH: That's all, Hannah.

34:29.862 --> 34:30.563
I'm leaving.

34:33.667 --> 34:35.936
This can be used

34:35.969 --> 34:37.804
to pierce rape shield,

34:37.838 --> 34:39.639
which is vulnerable
to begin with.

34:40.139 --> 34:41.474
You might want to consider

34:41.507 --> 34:43.143
sparing your daughter
this trial.

34:43.176 --> 34:44.878
WALSH: Hannah.

34:44.911 --> 34:45.846
Get out.

34:46.446 --> 34:48.014
Misdemeanor assault,

34:48.047 --> 34:51.317
one year suspended,
that's a gift.

34:51.351 --> 34:52.953
None of us wants
to go to trial here.

34:57.423 --> 34:59.359
(door opens)

34:59.392 --> 35:00.466
(door closes)

35:02.769 --> 35:04.237
And the D. A. Agreed?

35:04.270 --> 35:06.172
I just got the call.

35:06.206 --> 35:08.642
Your son does get a conviction.

35:08.675 --> 35:09.943
But no jail?

35:09.976 --> 35:11.578
Assuming the judge signs off,

35:11.612 --> 35:12.979
which he should.

35:13.013 --> 35:15.081
Oh, thank God.

35:15.115 --> 35:16.583
You can thank Hannah.

35:20.220 --> 35:21.522
I don't know what to say.

35:22.956 --> 35:26.292
He's a fine young man,
Ms. Rose, and...

35:28.228 --> 35:31.031
Mr. Solomon, I can see
you're having a moment.

35:31.998 --> 35:33.333
But for my take on the facts,

35:33.366 --> 35:35.335
which includes an interview
with the fine, young man,

35:35.368 --> 35:36.269
he's a rapist.

35:41.642 --> 35:43.409
If he's to make anything
of this second chance,

35:43.443 --> 35:45.145
daddy needs to see
the fine, young man

35:45.178 --> 35:46.513
for what he is

35:46.547 --> 35:48.414
and get him
into some counseling.

35:56.222 --> 35:57.257
HEEP: They're all nuts.

35:57.290 --> 35:57.991
QUINLEN: Who?

35:58.024 --> 35:59.259
The partners.

36:01.167 --> 36:02.636
They've all totally
had work done.

36:03.336 --> 36:04.170
They have?

36:04.204 --> 36:05.806
Please.
Denny Crane's head

36:05.839 --> 36:07.073
is so pumped full of Botox.

36:07.107 --> 36:08.675
Even Hannah, pretty Hannah.

36:09.075 --> 36:09.943
Hannah Rose?

36:09.976 --> 36:11.077
HEEP: Yeah.

36:11.111 --> 36:12.145
She's in her 30s.

36:12.178 --> 36:13.614
So what?
She's pulled so tight,

36:13.647 --> 36:14.848
she's got to cross
her legs to smile.

36:18.284 --> 36:19.252
Oh, my God.

36:21.522 --> 36:22.889
(sighs)

36:23.690 --> 36:25.859
I guess it's lucky
I don't like to smile.

36:25.892 --> 36:26.927
I was just--

36:28.829 --> 36:29.930
Oh, my God.

36:35.368 --> 36:37.270
How much do we pay you, Sally?

36:39.105 --> 36:40.541
$160,000.

36:41.241 --> 36:43.977
Do you think
we pay you $160,000

36:44.010 --> 36:45.378
to come down here
to the storage room

36:45.411 --> 36:46.513
and smoke pot, Sally?

36:47.147 --> 36:48.048
No, ma'am.

36:49.616 --> 36:51.885
It would be a mistake
to call me "Ma'am."

36:53.854 --> 36:55.288
Give me the joint, Sally.

36:57.591 --> 36:58.424
Do you need to pee, Mark?

36:58.458 --> 37:00.967
Yes, ma'am, sir,

37:01.000 --> 37:02.802
Hannah.

37:02.836 --> 37:03.537
God.

37:03.570 --> 37:05.539
Go pee, Mark.

37:11.277 --> 37:13.412
I, like,

37:13.446 --> 37:15.281
so miscalculated my day.

37:16.349 --> 37:19.285
I've had a lousy day, too, Sal.

37:19.319 --> 37:21.221
I arranged
for a rapist to get off

37:21.254 --> 37:22.989
with just a slap
on the wrist.

37:23.023 --> 37:25.058
Now I need to go
buy something

37:25.091 --> 37:26.593
to feel better
about myself.

37:28.461 --> 37:30.831
I've been eyeing
this little purse, actually,

37:30.864 --> 37:32.866
it costs $900.

37:32.899 --> 37:36.302
Can you imagine,
$900 for a purse?

37:38.071 --> 37:40.340
Luckily, I can afford it.

37:40.373 --> 37:42.976
Partners here are well paid.

37:43.009 --> 37:45.679
I bet you hope
to be partner one day.

37:51.518 --> 37:54.154
Complain about me
to anyone ever again,

37:54.187 --> 37:57.123
even to your own mother,

37:57.157 --> 38:00.634
this little pot incident,

38:00.667 --> 38:02.168
comes to light.

38:24.124 --> 38:25.659
What the hell
are you doing in my office?

38:29.295 --> 38:31.064
Had you there again,
didn't I, dad?

38:31.832 --> 38:34.668
I've asked you not to make fun
of my mental health.

38:34.701 --> 38:36.970
As I recall,

38:37.003 --> 38:38.404
I meant it.

38:40.373 --> 38:43.443
If I offended you before,
I apologize.

38:45.311 --> 38:46.680
You know, you don't fool me.

38:50.050 --> 38:51.852
My success as a trial attorney

38:51.885 --> 38:53.854
comes from my ability
to read people.

38:56.156 --> 38:57.390
I read you.

39:00.534 --> 39:03.103
I know your little secret,
soldier.

39:04.571 --> 39:05.338
You do?

39:05.371 --> 39:07.440
Mm-hmm.

39:07.473 --> 39:09.843
You're in awe of me.

39:13.880 --> 39:15.649
Well, now that the secret's out,

39:18.418 --> 39:20.253
let me tell you something,
Denny Crane,

39:22.723 --> 39:26.392
having watched you
at the courthouse yesterday,

39:26.426 --> 39:28.228
I just want you to know,

39:29.129 --> 39:30.196
I am in awe.

39:33.534 --> 39:34.768
You're Denny Crane,

39:37.871 --> 39:40.206
and that's...

39:40.240 --> 39:41.474
something.

39:56.022 --> 39:58.324
You've taken up
a minute of my time.

39:59.926 --> 40:02.068
To whom do I send the bill?

40:04.237 --> 40:05.606
Send the bill to me.

40:15.916 --> 40:17.150
Best thing is, it's elegant.

40:17.183 --> 40:19.352
You can go dressy,
and it's casual.

40:19.385 --> 40:22.122
It goes with a sweater
and jeans just as well.

40:22.155 --> 40:24.157
And the size...

40:24.190 --> 40:26.259
Do you like to carry
a lot of stuff?

40:26.292 --> 40:27.994
Totally.

40:28.028 --> 40:30.430
Let's go with the big one.

40:30.463 --> 40:31.732
Oh, I'm jealous.

40:31.765 --> 40:33.934
I've been saving up
to get this same bag.

40:33.967 --> 40:35.101
Well, look on the bright side,

40:35.135 --> 40:36.803
if I saw it on you,
I'd no longer want it.

40:38.572 --> 40:40.406
Tell you what.

40:40.440 --> 40:41.842
Give me half off,

40:41.875 --> 40:42.643
I'll buy you one.

40:42.676 --> 40:44.277
WATSON: If only I could.

40:44.310 --> 40:46.246
Look, if you get home,
and you suddenly hate it,

40:46.279 --> 40:48.081
bring it back,
no problem.

40:48.114 --> 40:49.750
Not supposed to say it.

40:49.783 --> 40:50.984
Never heard it.

40:54.387 --> 40:55.622
What's the matter?

40:58.391 --> 41:00.934
Hannah Rose?

41:00.967 --> 41:02.135
You're an attorney?

41:04.170 --> 41:05.038
Why?

41:06.406 --> 41:08.041
My name is Candace Watson.

41:10.476 --> 41:12.312
Your client raped me
last week.

41:22.388 --> 41:23.924
(scoffs)

41:23.957 --> 41:26.192
Small town, Boston.

41:27.828 --> 41:31.497
Just sign here, please,
and you're good to go.

41:33.834 --> 41:35.101
Look, I, uh,

41:38.772 --> 41:39.773
(sighs)

41:44.344 --> 41:47.280
(music playing)

42:19.252 --> 42:22.188
(music playing)

42:45.579 --> 42:46.713
WOMAN: You stinker!

42:46.747 --> 42:49.415
